01:20:18,500 --> 01:20:20,695
That is sport, my man.

540
01:20:22,504 --> 01:20:24,369
Look. Hum!

541
01:20:26,408 --> 01:20:28,899
Death is never the
end of a story.

542
01:20:29,044 --> 01:20:30,739
There are still traces.

543
01:20:33,182 --> 01:20:34,911
If you want to find
your brother,

544
01:20:35,050 --> 01:20:37,484
you'll have to go back into
your mother's past.

545
01:20:37,586 --> 01:20:40,180
Jean, I'm going to fetch my
sister, that's all.

546
01:20:40,322 --> 01:20:41,254
I'll take care of that.

547
01:20:41,390 --> 01:20:43,585
Two, three small matters
to take care,

548
01:20:43,726 --> 01:20:45,193
then it will take no time.

549
01:20:45,361 --> 01:20:47,090
Well, get your business ready

550
01:20:47,229 --> 01:20:48,491
we should go in ...

551
01:20:48,597 --> 01:20:50,497
My passport ...

552
01:20:50,599 --> 01:20:54,035
"We"? Don't you worry that
you already done enough already

553
01:20:54,169 --> 01:20:57,366
Exactly, this is not the
time to let you down.

554
01:20:59,341 --> 01:21:01,036
Make a man out of you, Simon.

555
01:21:01,176 --> 01:21:03,371
I know that you need me.

556
01:21:06,181 --> 01:21:07,773
We'll get it, then come back.

557
01:21:07,916 --> 01:21:09,281
I promise.

558
01:21:09,418 --> 01:21:11,443
Then, promise, Mr. Marwan,

559
01:21:11,587 --> 01:21:14,750
a notary is on the order
of the sacred.

560
01:24:10,732 --> 01:24:12,859
Sing now.

561
01:25:19,668 --> 01:25:22,034
Gently, gently.

562
01:25:24,172 --> 01:25:25,537
He is coming out.

563
01:25:25,941 --> 01:25:27,340
We can see the head.

564
01:25:27,509 --> 01:25:28,874
Push, push.

565
01:25:29,511 --> 01:25:31,103
Go, girl.

566
01:25:39,454 --> 01:25:41,046
The first came out.

567
01:26:02,010 --> 01:26:05,241
Rest now ...

568
01:26:06,348 --> 01:26:07,713
I'm proud of you.

569
01:26:09,651 --> 01:26:11,676
Get ready for the second.

570
01:26:41,116 --> 01:26:42,378
Stop.

571
01:26:42,617 --> 01:26:43,948
Stop.

572
01:26:45,120 --> 01:26:46,052
What are you doing?

573
01:26:46,388 --> 01:26:48,618
You are going to dump them in the
river as usual.

574
01:26:50,425 --> 01:26:51,722
- It's dangerous.
- No.

575
01:26:51,860 --> 01:26:55,796
You've done your duty.
Throw them in the river.

576
01:26:55,964 --> 01:26:57,591
I want to take care of them.

577
01:26:58,066 --> 01:27:00,626
These are the children of
the woman who sings.

578
01:27:20,622 --> 01:27:23,750
Oh, this country is a war
zone after another, eh!

579
01:27:23,925 --> 01:27:24,983
It's not complicated.

580
01:27:25,127 --> 01:27:27,618
If the notary had existed
at the time of Noah,

581
01:27:27,763 --> 01:27:28,923
we would not be here.

582
01:27:29,064 --> 01:27:31,828
We need only to find the
original contracts.

583
01:27:31,967 --> 01:27:35,596
That's up to you, that's up to you.
And a right of passage there.

584
01:27:35,737 --> 01:27:36,726
And we talk more about it.

585
01:27:36,838 --> 01:27:38,271
Everyone would be happy.

586
01:27:38,440 --> 01:27:41,238
Notaries have existed
only in the last 1,000 years, Simon.

587
01:27:41,343 --> 01:27:43,004
That's the problem.

588
01:27:43,145 --> 01:27:45,272
I should have been here from
the beginning.

589
01:27:45,414 --> 01:27:48,144
Thank you again for your
help, Me Maddad.

590
01:27:48,283 --> 01:27:50,808
The pleasure is all
mine, my dear fellow.

591
01:27:50,952 --> 01:27:52,613
I have the result

592
01:27:52,754 --> 01:27:54,688
that you have requested
via email.

593
01:27:54,823 --> 01:27:57,451
Simon my file on
the seat beside you.

594
01:27:57,592 --> 01:28:00,425
Could you give it to
Lebel, please?

595
01:28:00,529 --> 01:28:03,464
You are very nice, but the
delay and everything ...

596
01:28:03,598 --> 01:28:05,862
I think I'll wait until later.

597
01:28:06,001 --> 01:28:07,195
But I'll summarize.

598
01:28:07,335 --> 01:28:08,962
For the father, it is
rather difficult

599
01:28:09,137 --> 01:28:11,037
because I can not find
the death certificate.

600
01:28:11,173 --> 01:28:12,140
For the brother ...

601
01:28:12,274 --> 01:28:14,139
Excuse me, but what
are we talking about here?

602
01:28:14,309 --> 01:28:15,970
I asked for help, Simon.

603
01:28:16,144 --> 01:28:18,874
Me Maddad kindly gave us a hand

604
01:28:19,014 --> 01:28:20,345
to speed things up.

605
01:28:20,482 --> 01:28:23,781
I told you, Jean,
we came for Jeanne.

606
01:28:25,153 --> 01:28:27,815
Your sister is the one person
in your family

607
01:28:27,989 --> 01:28:29,388
easiest to find.

608
01:28:36,565 --> 01:28:39,033
I'm so glad you're here.

609
01:28:39,167 --> 01:28:41,328
Me too.

610
01:28:47,876 --> 01:28:49,844
OK, that's the nurse's name.

611
01:28:50,011 --> 01:28:51,842
which helped your mother give birth
in prison.

612
01:28:51,980 --> 01:28:53,538
We can go today.

613
01:28:54,549 --> 01:28:56,847
Jeanne, that's enough.

614
01:28:58,720 --> 01:29:00,688
No, you shut up, then follow me.

615
01:29:00,856 --> 01:29:03,757
It's your job to find our
brother, not mine!

616
01:29:03,892 --> 01:29:06,190
Then, if you don't do it for
her or for you,

617
01:29:06,361 --> 01:29:08,056
the, do it for me!

618
01:29:14,236 --> 01:29:16,033
She is at the American hospital.

619
01:29:22,177 --> 01:29:23,940
I'm glad you're here, Jean.

620
01:29:24,079 --> 01:29:26,013
Me too, my owl, me too.

621
01:29:27,082 --> 01:29:29,380
If she is sleeping, you must return
later.

622
01:29:53,808 --> 01:29:55,298
Ms. Maika?

623
01:30:24,066 --> 01:30:27,229
Lebel, Jeanne Marwan,
Simon Marwan.

624
01:30:27,403 --> 01:30:28,768
Bonjour, Madame!

625
01:30:28,904 --> 01:30:30,394
Thank you for having us.

626
01:30:30,572 --> 01:30:33,405
We seek someone you know.

627
01:30:33,542 --> 01:30:35,772
Nawal Marwan, do you know her?

628
01:31:03,939 --> 01:31:06,806
You worked in the Kfar Ryat prison
as a nurse?

629
01:31:21,290 --> 01:31:23,588
She says she knows your mom.

630
01:31:24,793 --> 01:31:27,023
You helped our mother
give birth in prison?

631
01:31:31,633 --> 01:31:32,964
Yes.

632
01:31:39,608 --> 01:31:43,305
Madame, the child we seek is Nawal
Marwan's son that was born in prison.

633
01:31:43,479 --> 01:31:44,878
Can you help us?

634
01:31:48,517 --> 01:31:51,850
She worked in the prison
of Kfar Ryat.

635
01:31:52,988 --> 01:31:55,548
She assisted her
during childbirth.

636
01:31:56,992 --> 01:31:58,983
She gathered the children.

637
01:32:05,801 --> 01:32:08,463
Then she gave them back
to the woman who sings

638
01:32:08,570 --> 01:32:10,504
when she got out of prison.

639
01:32:11,707 --> 01:32:13,834
Nawal Marwan gave
birth to twins.

640
01:32:16,745 --> 01:32:18,212
Hush, hush, hush.

641
01:32:20,315 --> 01:32:22,180
Hush, hush, hush.

642
01:36:28,764 --> 01:36:31,426
You really know the
woman who sings?

643
01:36:31,566 --> 01:36:34,592
You don't know what
it means to me.

644
01:36:35,771 --> 01:36:37,739
Nawal Marwan worked for me

645
01:36:37,839 --> 01:36:39,431
as a secretary for 18 years.

646
01:36:39,574 --> 01:36:41,804
My wife and I, we had
taken a liking

647
01:36:41,943 --> 01:36:43,433
to her and her children.

648
01:36:44,446 --> 01:36:45,777
But I confess that I

649
01:36:45,947 --> 01:36:48,438
didn't really know her till the end.

650
01:36:51,119 --> 01:36:53,280
- Ready?
- Ready.

651
01:37:05,333 --> 01:37:06,823
Hmm ...

652
01:37:08,470 --> 01:37:10,961
Me Maddadi has conducted an
investigation, at my request,

653
01:37:11,139 --> 01:37:14,302
to track your brother
and your father.

654
01:37:19,815 --> 01:37:21,442
For the father, Abu Tarek,

655
01:37:21,550 --> 01:37:24,314
I still have not found
a death certificate.

656
01:37:24,486 --> 01:37:26,613
The country has a lot
of certificates missing.

657
01:37:26,721 --> 01:37:28,951
He could have gone abroad.

658
01:37:29,057 --> 01:37:32,356
That's what happened with
this kind of characters.

659
01:37:32,494 --> 01:37:33,893
They are dead or have disappeared.

660
01:37:34,029 --> 01:37:35,155
You have to see.

661
01:37:35,330 --> 01:37:37,491
Maybe it's better that way.

662
01:37:38,533 --> 01:37:40,899
For the brother ...

663
01:37:41,036 --> 01:37:43,334
your client, Ms. Nawal Marwan,

664
01:37:43,471 --> 01:37:45,336
comes from the village
of Der Om.

665
01:37:45,507 --> 01:37:49,739
She gave the child to a midwife
who's named Elham

666
01:37:49,878 --> 01:37:53,678
who herself returned it to
the orphanage in Kfar Kout

667
01:37:53,849 --> 01:37:56,181
in May 1970.

668
01:37:57,519 --> 01:38:00,386
The main task was to
trace the registry records.

669
01:38:00,522 --> 01:38:03,082
Many documents have been
lost in the war.

670
01:38:04,092 --> 01:38:06,686
But I found the records

671
01:38:06,828 --> 01:38:09,092
which were recovered and donated

672
01:38:09,231 --> 01:38:13,361
by the Sisters of Charity
to the National Archives.

673
01:38:13,501 --> 01:38:17,198
In May 1970, the midwife at
Der Om, Elham

674
01:38:17,372 --> 01:38:20,205
filed a petition for adoption
of a male child.

675
01:38:20,342 --> 01:38:25,006
This is the only boy in the
orphanage filed in that month.

676
01:38:25,113 --> 01:38:26,444
Look.

677
01:38:26,581 --> 01:38:29,744
It was registered under
the name Nihad.

678
01:38:31,586 --> 01:38:33,713
The dates match.

679
01:38:33,855 --> 01:38:35,345
That's him.

680
01:38:36,358 --> 01:38:39,521
Ha! It's your brother! Nihad.

681
01:38:43,064 --> 01:38:45,055
Orphanage Kfar Kout,

682
01:38:45,200 --> 01:38:46,258
Nihad May.

683
01:38:46,401 --> 01:38:49,461
It's his name in the registry.

684
01:38:49,604 --> 01:38:50,798
Nihad from the month of May.

685
01:38:50,939 --> 01:38:53,373
They gave him a temporary name

686
01:38:53,475 --> 01:38:54,806
with the month of arrival.

687
01:38:54,943 --> 01:38:57,969
There was no adoption
during that period.

688
01:38:58,113 --> 01:38:59,910
It was the beginning of the war.

689
01:39:00,081 --> 01:39:02,811
The orphanage was destroyed
four years later.

690
01:39:04,085 --> 01:39:06,747
We must ask those that destroyed
the orphanage in Kfar Kout

691
01:39:06,888 --> 01:39:09,755
to know what happened
to the children.

692
01:39:11,760 --> 01:39:15,423
Between you and me, with what
happened in the region ...

693
01:39:16,431 --> 01:39:17,921
there is not much hope.

694
01:39:19,401 --> 01:39:21,426
They are probably also dead.

695
01:39:21,569 --> 01:39:23,628
I'm not saying they're dead.

696
01:39:23,772 --> 01:39:25,899
I say we lost track of them.

697
01:39:27,609 --> 01:39:29,440
They are both dead.

698
01:39:29,577 --> 01:39:32,011
We open the envelopes,
that's it, then.

699
01:39:32,147 --> 01:39:33,978
That I will not allow, Simon.

700
01:39:34,115 --> 01:39:35,946
This kind of thing is sacred.

701
01:39:39,788 --> 01:39:41,983
Luckily, I have a history.

702
01:39:44,693 --> 01:39:46,786
Excuse me.

703
01:39:48,430 --> 01:39:50,523
It is still worth exploring.

704
01:39:50,665 --> 01:39:53,930
But it is a little radical.

705
01:39:54,970 --> 01:39:55,937
The warlord

706
01:39:56,037 --> 01:39:58,665
that demolished the orphanage
at that time is still alive.

707
01:39:58,807 --> 01:40:00,866
And he may know what happened

708
01:40:01,009 --> 01:40:03,204
to Nihad's children and where
they went.

709
01:40:03,345 --> 01:40:04,539
It's already been an eternity.

710
01:40:04,679 --> 01:40:06,340
You must understand

711
01:40:06,481 --> 01:40:09,678
that during this period there were
a series of reprisals

712
01:40:09,818 --> 01:40:13,345
which fit one another in
a sort of inexorable logic,

713
01:40:17,325 --> 01:40:19,293
A warlord is exactly

714
01:40:19,394 --> 01:40:21,555
the type of man who
has a long memory.

715
01:40:21,696 --> 01:40:24,028
And he will remember, believe me.

716
01:40:25,467 --> 01:40:27,298
Wallat Chamseddine,

717
01:40:27,402 --> 01:40:28,835
is his name.

718
01:40:33,141 --> 01:40:34,506
We can find him here?

719
01:40:34,642 --> 01:40:37,634
If we don't find him, he
will find us.

720
01:40:40,515 --> 01:40:42,540
But we can try something.

721
01:40:44,386 --> 01:40:47,048
Would you like tea, Mr. Marwan?

722
01:40:51,059 --> 01:40:53,027
It's your turn.

723
01:40:56,498 --> 01:40:58,227
You will go

724
01:40:58,366 --> 01:41:00,357
to the Deressa refugee camp.

725
01:41:00,535 --> 01:41:02,002
You will come to tea

726
01:41:02,103 --> 01:41:03,365
anywhere in the camp

727
01:41:03,538 --> 01:41:05,403
with the person that invite you.

728
01:41:05,540 --> 01:41:08,532
And you say you are the son
of the woman who sings

729
01:41:08,676 --> 01:41:10,541
and are looking Nihad May.

730
01:41:10,712 --> 01:41:12,839
You can not go there alone.

731
01:41:14,115 --> 01:41:16,208
I'll find someone

732
01:41:16,351 --> 01:41:17,875
to accompany you.

733
01:41:39,974 --> 01:41:41,737
Welcome to Deressa.

734
01:42:50,311 --> 01:42:52,142
Ha! Ha! You know where you
are going, Simon?

735
01:42:52,313 --> 01:42:53,712
I know.

736
01:43:20,074 --> 01:43:21,302
How are you?

737
01:43:22,644 --> 01:43:24,134
In the name of God, you've grown!

738
01:43:24,312 --> 01:43:27,076
I have finished my engineering studies.

739
01:43:27,248 --> 01:43:31,878
I cannot find work, so I'm
a taxi driver now.

740
01:43:32,053 --> 01:43:34,078
What brings you here?

741
01:43:34,255 --> 01:43:39,318
I am with some foreign visitors, who
asked me to bring them here.

742
01:43:41,196 --> 01:43:43,061
Welcome, come.

743
01:43:43,231 --> 01:43:45,563
No, thank you, we're
in a hurry.

744
01:43:45,733 --> 01:43:47,564
Please, come.

745
01:43:52,874 --> 01:43:55,604
He is inviting us to tea.

746
01:43:55,743 --> 01:43:56,869
Oh, good!

747
01:44:14,095 --> 01:44:17,929
Uh, I wonder why you have
come to Deressa.

748
01:44:21,069 --> 01:44:23,560
I am looking for someone
named Nihad de Mai.

749
01:44:32,914 --> 01:44:35,906
He does not know Nihad de Mai.

750
01:44:36,050 --> 01:44:39,247
He asks me what are your names.

751
01:44:46,594 --> 01:44:49,427
My mother comes from the village
of Der de Om, in the South.

752
01:45:02,677 --> 01:45:04,770
My mother is the woman who sings.

753
01:45:30,171 --> 01:45:32,264
Yes, that's fine. Done.

754
01:45:37,445 --> 01:45:39,003
Wait for what?

755
01:46:12,347 --> 01:46:14,315
- Sarwan Marwan?
- Yes.

756
01:46:14,415 --> 01:46:16,747
We are here to offer help.

757
01:46:16,884 --> 01:46:19,182
You will be back in an hour.

758
01:46:20,421 --> 01:46:21,911
Can I tell my sister?

759
01:46:22,056 --> 01:46:25,082
No, you'll be back in
an hour, I promise.

760
01:46:26,561 --> 01:46:29,029
I'll put on a shirt, just a second.

761
01:46:31,833 --> 01:46:33,027
He will call.

762
01:46:33,401 --> 01:46:34,766
He's going to go.

763
01:46:35,436 --> 01:46:38,269
Ok! Do not worry, you can follow.

764
01:46:38,406 --> 01:46:41,842
Ah, I told you: the South,
a spark and it exploded.

765
01:46:42,043 --> 01:46:43,442
Oh, okay.

766
01:47:57,685 --> 01:48:00,950
You have been luck with us,
we'll help in our own way.

767
01:48:02,323 --> 01:48:03,847
You must leave the country.

768
01:48:04,025 --> 01:48:05,754
It'll be easier.

769
01:48:05,927 --> 01:48:08,361
We will find you a house and a job.

770
01:48:09,297 --> 01:48:12,289
I want your life to be better.

771
01:48:14,101 --> 01:48:16,865
We have many contacts
in America.

772
01:48:18,673 --> 01:48:20,868
You gotta go with your children.

773
01:48:21,476 --> 01:48:24,309
I know they are alive.
Take them with you.

774
01:48:27,482 --> 01:48:31,145
The children will help
you, you'll see.

775
01:48:37,959 --> 01:48:40,894
You cannot ask me.

776
01:48:42,730 --> 01:48:45,028
Your children are our
children, Nawal.

777
01:48:45,199 --> 01:48:47,326
Your family is our family.

778
01:48:47,835 --> 01:48:49,029
Trust me.

779
01:48:50,471 --> 01:48:53,406
I'll help you.

780
01:48:53,574 --> 01:48:56,907
I'm here for you and
your children.

781
01:49:46,427 --> 01:49:47,917
Hello, Sarwan.

782
01:49:50,064 --> 01:49:53,727
Excuse my introduction, but
it is for your protection.

783
01:49:55,903 --> 01:49:58,804
They call me Wallat Chamseddine.

784
01:50:01,208 --> 01:50:05,542
Tell me, what can I do to
help, Sarwan Marwan?

785
01:50:07,281 --> 01:50:09,044
You knew my mother.

786
01:50:09,150 --> 01:50:11,778
They say she worked for me.

787
01:50:11,919 --> 01:50:14,945
What can I do to help?

788
01:50:18,926 --> 01:50:22,259
I am looking for a
man named Nihad de Mai.

789
01:50:23,297 --> 01:50:25,424
Why you are looking for Nihad de Mai?

790
01:50:27,435 --> 01:50:28,493
He's my brother.

791
01:50:28,636 --> 01:50:31,127
My mother asked me to find him.

792
01:50:32,840 --> 01:50:34,671
And how can you prove that

793
01:50:34,809 --> 01:50:37,835
Nihad de Mai is the son
of Nawal Marwan?

794
01:50:40,615 --> 01:50:42,412
My brother was
placed for adoption

795
01:50:42,516 --> 01:50:44,279
at the Kfar Kout orphanage.

796
01:50:45,620 --> 01:50:48,589
We found the registry with
the original file.

797
01:50:49,590 --> 01:50:51,251
The dates ... Everything fits.

798
01:50:51,359 --> 01:50:53,589
Nihad de Mai is my brother.

799
01:51:36,837 --> 01:51:38,896
Me and my friends, we attacked

800
01:51:39,040 --> 01:51:41,372
the christian village at Kfar Kout ...

801
01:51:42,376 --> 01:51:43,843
